reviews.text: The pink room is so lovely. We did the dim sum and it was high quality food! The lobster noodles were delicious. And the dim sum was quite good as well. The tea is good too and they gave us various tea pots upon request. The service was very good and the staff was highly attentive. They didn't rush us out, which was great! There were people doing bridal showers, baby sprinkles, and afternoon tea.

The place has great food and great seating arrangements, especially if you are asking for one of the private rooms. The drinks are also a wonder. The one thing that makes this hard to recommend is the price tag. It's very hard to recommend unless someone else is paying, or you're on a special occasion and have a high salary to start. A luxury rather than a regular grazing ground.

One of my favourite Chinese weekend brunch. Food is delicious, great service and an amazing view. Seatings outside makes atmosphere for chili all day. One thang you must order is Peking duck, it is so delicious. Don’t forget to reserve a table especially if you want to sit outside on the balcony.
It's little too pricey but nice. Staffs are kind. Dishes are fine.

This restaurant is a gem! The food is amazing and the staff super friendly! I have been here several times for lunch and for dinner and I can`t get enough of their truffle chicken, Kung Pao prawns and the pork belly! It`s also my favorite verandah in HK to bring friends and clients for drinks! Highly recommended!

reviews.text:
Men are easy to figure out, right? They just want sex. Then they want love and attention. Figure that out and you’ll have a man for life!
The only problem is…it doesn’t always work out that way. Sometimes men want something MORE than just sex, more than just attention and “love”…or at least the love that you think they feel. Love is very confusing and it’s so tightly intertwined with a man’s ego and id, that it’s very often hard to understand. Just because a man feels strong emotion doesn’t necessarily mean he’s in love. Just because a man is willing to TRY a relationship with you doesn’t mean he’s actually ready to go all the way and give you the marriage and family commitment you really want.
Now granted, although every man is an individual with unique attributes, it’s also safe to say that a wide variety of men DO exhibit some of the same characteristic behavior. In other words, they all behave and react in similar ways, suggesting either some sort of herd mentality instinct or perhaps it’s just cultural influences, since I mostly write about the North American male mindset.
But one thing’s for sure…

A refreshing concept of touring the museum by role playing characters of the past. A good depth of Hong Kong's Police force history can be experienced over here. You can easily spend a good 2 hours at this place. Coupled with restaurant, bar and shop, it makes a great afternoon to evening outing.

This whole place used to be a police station/prison, but there are still a few policemen still use a small space. It is a full of history & it is worth to visit. It's free most places except a few modern buildings you have to pay to get in which I didn't go in.

What an interesting place to check out! It exhibits the buildings and objects from the police station and jail in the old time (1840 till late last century, and yes, they were physically connected).
We had a great time there browsing around. And we bumped into a police parade which surprised us with beautiful music from the bagpipes.
Definitely worth coming and checjing out. Highly recommend.
Very cool to walk around!! Nice historical place. Could spend a couple of hours easily if you wanted to see everything.

Sono stato a Hong Kong un'infinità di volte e ho provato una gran varietà di buoni ristoranti. Ma qui siamo all'eccellenza, per la qualità straordinaria dei piatti, cucinati con estrema raffinatezza, e la bellezza sorprendente del posto, ricavato dalla ristrutturazione di un intero quartiere, sede di una ex centrale di Polizia con annesso carcere. Ora ospita ristoranti, bar, caffè, negozi e boutique. Un posto da visitare assolutamente e un ristorante da non mancare, per chi ama la grande cucina.

The place has great food and great seating arrangements, especially if you are asking for one of the private rooms. The drinks are also a wonder. The one thing that makes this hard to recommend is the price tag. It's very hard to recommend unless someone else is paying, or you're on a special occasion and have a high salary to start. A luxury rather than a regular grazing ground.
